fielddes: Unique ID assigned to a Location. A Location is a physical address associated with an Organization, which may be used for legal and/or business purposes.
ID of the Organization associated with the Location.

Primary name of the Organization, derived from multiple sources including the IRS, Dept. of Labor, SEC, SBA, and local jurisdictions. A waterfall is in place to pick the Organization's primary name, with preference given to IRS related sources.
TICKER of the Organization if it is publicly listed.

Link to the Organization's primary website. A company's website is not usually included in the regulatory filings, but BQ uses alternative methods to identify these links, which may result in occasional inaccuracies.
Name of the Location, often a DBA.
This refers to whether the Location is a Headquarters, Ultimate Parent Legal Entity, Child Legal Entity, Officer, Independent, or Branch.
This refers to whether the Location is a Business, Legal, Officer Person, or Officer Company address.
1st line of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
2nd line of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
City of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State abbreviation of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
State name of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
5-digit zip code of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
9-digit zip code (ZIP + 4) of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Zip code classification of the Location's address stating whether it is a P.O. Box or not. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County name of the Location's saddress. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
County-level FIPS code of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Country of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
RDI indicates whether the Location's address is Residential, Commercial, P.O. Box or Unknown based on USPS reporting.
Latitude of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Longitude of the Location's address. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.
Indicator that states "Yes" if the Location's address is verified to be deliverable based on the Delivery Point Validation Process of USPS.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Location's address is the "default" address for a building ( i.e., the main lobby) and 0 otherwise. Addresses are cleaned and standardized using USPS.

The Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) is a 5-digit numeric code which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Location's address lies according to USPS.
Name of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) which identifies the Metropolitan Statistical Area or Micropolitan Statistical Area in which the Location's address lies according to USPS.
Metro or Micro Type classification of the Core-Based Statistical Area (CBSA) in which the Location's address lies according to USPS.
Classification that indicates whether the Location's address is Match-Mailable or Non-Mailable based on USPS reporting.
Phone number associated with the Location.
The primary industry category of the Location, often very specific (e.g., food truck, nail salon), typically as submitted by the business owner in online review sites.
A score that denotes the aggregate quality and veracity of filings and online review site information associated with this Location.
All industry categories of the Location, often very specific (e.g., food truck, nail salon), typically as submitted by the business owner in online review sites.
Congressional disctrict name associated with the Location Address.
Count of the number of reviews for that Location in online review sites.
Average score of reviews for that Location in online review sites.
Website of the Location in online review sites, typically as submitted by the business owner.
Domain of the Location in online review sites, typically as submitted by the business owner.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Location is active and 0 otherwise.
Indicator that equals 1 if the Location is a Headquarter addresss and 0 otherwise.
